The paper deals with the problem of estimating values of a vector from a randomized sparse binary linear sketch, which is a problem related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses applications of the algorithm, which involve machine learning (cs.LG), social networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
